         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">Memo. for the Director of the Botanic Gardens. ¶  ¶ The Chief Secretary's attention has been called to a letter in "The Argus" of yesterday's date signed W. Fergusson and written apparently from the B...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">70.05.21a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From William Odgers</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">No. 1226, unit 20, p. 2, VPRS 1187/P outward registered correspondence, VA 475 Chief Secretary's, Public Record Office, Victoria.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Memo. for the Director of the Botanic Gardens.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The Chief Secretary's attention has been called to a letter in "The Argus" of yesterday's date signed W. Fergusson and written apparently from the Botanic Gardens.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn0" n="1">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="">
                           <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        </seg>'Destruction of trees in the Botanical Reserve',<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>, 20 May 1870, p. 5., signed 'William Ferguson' using the address 'Melbourne Botanic Gardens'.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M to J. McCulloch, 25 May 1870 is his reply<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>to this memo.</p>
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>M had sought permisson to respond to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Argus</seg>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>report<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>in<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>M to W. Odgers, 20 May 1870 (in this edition as 70-05-20c)<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>but<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>was refused<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>(W.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Odgers to M, 21 May 1870).<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                     </p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
               <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Sir Jas. McCulloch desires to know if Mr. Fergusson who holds the office of Inspector of State Forests &amp;c is the author of the letter in question and if so what explanation he has to offer for this violation of the 21st Civil Service Regulation.<seg rend="FootnoteReference" style="font-size: 8pt; ">
                  <note type="footnote" xml:id="_ftn1" n="2">
                     <p rend="FootnoteText"
                        style="margin-left: 0.3333in; text-indent: -0.3333in; font-size: 9pt; hyphenate: false; "
                        xml:lang="en">
                        <space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>
                        <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>'21.<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Communications Not to be Made to the Public<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>Press. — No officer shall make any communication,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>directly or indirectly, to the press upon any matter<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>affecting the department in which he serves, or the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>business or the officers thereof, or relating to the<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>public service, or his own official position or acts,<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>or upon any political subject or question whatso<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>ever, without the express permission or authority of<space unit="chars" quantity="1"/>the responsible Minister' (<seg rend="DefaultParagraphFont" style="font-style: italic; ">Victoria Government Gazette</seg>, 8 January 1867, p. 38).</p>
                  </note>
               </seg>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">W. H. Odgers</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">Chief Secretary's Office</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-size: 12pt; hyphenate: false; "
               xml:lang="en">21st May 1870.</p>
